<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-08-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-08-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="193" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d193">
                        <head>No. 138.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-08-26"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 26,
                                1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>O’Mahoney was discharged 4th of August. Case of Brophy is being
                            considered. Have heard nothing from Secretary of Ireland concerning
                            cases of Meany or George.</p>
                        <closer><signed>LOWELL.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>